  "@id": "tae-012",
  "@type": "Organization",
  "source": "un",
  "names": [
    {
      "name": "HAQQANI NETWORK (HQN)",
      "is_primary": true
    }
  ],
  "addresses": [],
  "remarks": "Network of Taliban fighters centered around the border between Khost\nProvince, Afghanistan and North Waziristan, Pakistan. Founded by Jalaluddin Haqqani\n(TAi.040) and currently headed by his son Sirajuddin Jallaloudine Haqqani (TAi.144).\nOther listed members include Nasiruddin Haqqani (TAi.146), Sangeen Zadran Sher Mohammad\n(TAi.152), Abdul Aziz Abbasin (TAi.155), Fazl Rabi (TAi.157), Ahmed Jan Wazir (TAi.159),\nBakht Gul (TAi.161), Abdul Rauf Zakir (TAi.164). Responsible for suicide attacks and\ntargeted assassination as well as kidnappings in Kabul and other provinces of\nAfghanistan. Linked to Al-Qaida (QDe.004), Islamic Movement of Uzbekistan (QDe.010),\nTehrik-e Taliban Pakistan (QDe.132), Lashkar I Jhangvi (QDe.096), and Jaish-IMohammed\n(QDe.019). INTERPOL-UN Security Council Special Notice web link:https://www.interpol.int/en/How-we-work/Notices/View-UN-Notices-Individuals"
}